    "Perry taught at several colleges and universities including Howard University, however, the majority of her professional career was spent at the Virginia Commonwealth University (formerly the Richmond Professional Institute), beginning in 1967.": [],
    "Perry was a professor of art history here for 25 years, retiring in 1990.": [],
    "During her tenure at VCU, Perry took leaves to develop her collection of Black art; beyond educating, Perry\u2019s passion lay in collecting and documenting Black art, often forgotten in traditional art scholarship.": [
